<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 4:50PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central
Washington and southwestern Iron Counties through 515 PM MDT...
At 450 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles northeast of Beaver Dam, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Enterprise and Newcastle.
This includes the following highways...
Utah Route 18 between mile markers 39 and 51.
Utah Route 56 between mile markers 22 and 32.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
